attentional lapses to individual differences in visual working memory capacity.
J Cogn Neurosci, 27(8), 1601-1616. doi:10.1162/jocn_a_00811</p>

<p>2.     
Christoff,
K., Irving, Z. C., Fox, K. C., Spreng, R. N., &amp; Andrews-Hanna, J. R.
(2016). Mind-wandering as spontaneous thought: a dynamic framework. Nat Rev
Neurosci, 17(11), 718-731. doi:10.1038/nrn.2016.113</p>

<p>3.     
Fortenbaugh,
F. C., DeGutis, J., &amp; Esterman, M. (2017). Recent theoretical, neural, and
clinical advances in sustained attention research. Ann N Y Acad Sci.
doi:10.1111/nyas.13318</p>

